content:
Peta, since when does lack of a rational line of thought doesn't necessitate scum?  I can understand being annoyed at Pine's play style, but do you actually think he's scum or just not like the way he's playing?<br>
<br>
@FuDuzn. Peta + crypto are buddy buddy because they are likely friends from outside the game. I wouldn't read much into it other than that they may be able to fool each other easier than normal.

^This post reads town to me.<br>
<br>
@EPM: As far as I can remember, <a href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?f=23&amp;t=17742" class="postlink">this</a> is my last scum game. You can find a few others in my wiki.

Doomyoshi replaces Servanto!<br>
<br>
Seriously tell your friends about replacing in &gt;_&gt;

@Doom, Gregory's aggression doesn't seem to have a scum agenda to it. The way he went after me/bvoight during RVS and his reads in #10 just come off as sincere.  Eh, when I think about it maybe he's not conf-town. I'm not really suspicious of him, but I could be biased because his reads have been similar to mine (particularly on epm/pine) and I tend to think people who have similar apparent mindsets as me to be likely town.<br>
<br>
I don't really want to go into the whole "defense of Pine" argument again. What I was defending was the wagon on Pine which I thought was pretty weak given Pine's meta. That's it. I didn't think there was any reason to be calling for blood.

@Denis, I still feel Tammy's attitude is fake. The "anger" is out of check with the circumstances, not just today but throughout the game really, and she's moving back and forth between analyzing and raging too seamlessly really. I know when I'm raging its like FULLBLOWNAIDSRAGING, I just don't believe the whole fuck it lynch me attitude she portrays only sometimes. To me, it seems like a convenient defense mechanism that she's used since replacing in and for what is supposedly an emotional appeal it comes off as hella calculated to me. I get how it could come off as town, but only if its an actual townie raging, ya know? And I get that Gregory-interactions might make more sense, but I can't shake this feeling that Tammy is scum here =/ <br>
<br>
Denis + FuDuzn are take it to the bank town btw.

@Fu. Eh, NLing doesn't hurt, but yea, EPM's "let's end this game" looks kind of like an admission to me. I'm at work atm, and I want to look things over one more time before voting. I'm pretty sure in thinking its EPM but I want to look at a few more things first. And yea NLing is generally a good rule with 4 left, but like you said not much would change tomorrow, either you or I would die and we'd still be looking at the same situation.<br>
<br>
pedit: why do you want to end the game EPM? Right now it looks like you are going to be lynched and I like to think I'm pretty good at figuring things out late game and I try to keep an open mind...Can you explain why in a mylo situation you'd make a vote for me if you weren't set on it? I'd think if you thought I was scum you'd be saying that in thread and then wanting to NL, seemed strange to me. Plus it doesn't have to be walls or anything, but at least somt specific examples of Tammy's play that are getting your vote right now would be helpful
